      "body" : "I agree. The patch above doesn't go far enough since the client still thinks the thread is running.\r\n\r\nPrior to checkpoints - yes it should always forbid any mining while there are still checkpointed blocks that haven't been synced. Mining is meaningless in this context. \r\n\r\nBut _beyond_ the last checkpoint and prior to syncing _everything_, is slightly less of an issue. It won't hit this specific error, and hell, if they're lucky they'll outdo everyone else (heh). ",
